cs.SE, cs.SD, cs.PL, cs.CY, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the documentation practices and challenges of non-functional requirements (NFRs) in agile software development (ASD), which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also proposes guidelines for enhancing NFRs documentation in ASD, which involves software development (cs.SD), programming languages (cs.PL), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
